Description. Male (MACN-Ar 29452).
Carapace and chelicerae reddish brown (
Fig. 50A
). Endites brownish orange; labium dark brownish orange. Sternum brownish orange, with darker margins, marbled with dark pigment, and three pairs of fainted dark marginal areas (
Fig. 50B
). Palps light orange (
Fig. 51A‒B
). Legs brownish orange, pairs I‒II darker with dark pigment forming diffuse rings in the distal region of metatarsus (
Fig. 50C‒E
). Abdomen whitish grey, with a conspicuous dark dorsal pattern comprising arrow-shaped marks (
Fig. 50A‒B
). Total length 7.24; carapace 3.44 long, 2.24 wide. Palps: tibia incrassated, with the dorso-ventral diameter slightly shorter than the bulb; cymbium with a dorsal chemosensory patch; bulb rounded, mid-portion about two times shorter than the embolus; transition mid-portion/embolus conspicuous; embolus tubular and tapered (
Fig. 51A‒B
). Legs: robust and densely coated with setae (
Fig. 50C‒E
); tarsal brush of putative chemosensory setae present in legs I‒III, but reduced. Leg formula: I-II-IV-III. Leg measurements: I, femur 2.88, patella 1.24, tibia 2.6, metatarsus 2.76, tarsus 0.72, total 10.2; II, 2.6, 1.28, 2.76, 2.64, 0.72, 10.0; III, 2.04, 1.0, 1.6, 1.6, 0.56, 6.8; IV, 2.32, 1.08, 2.04, 1.76, 0.6, 7.8. Macrosetae: I, femur d0-0-0-0-1-1/2-0, p0-0-0-0-2-1-0; patella p0-1-0; tibia d0/1-2/1-0-2-0-1/2-0, p0-0-0-1-0- 1-0, vp1-0-1-0-1-0-1, vr2-0-1-0-1-0-1, r1-1-1-1-1-1-0; metatarsus vp1-0-0-1(reduced/apophysis)-0-0-1, vr0-0-0-1- 0-0-1 (
Fig. 50C‒E
); II, femur d0-1/0-0-1-0-1-0-2-0, p0-0-0-0-0-0-1-1-0; patella p0-1-0; tibia d0-0-0-1-0-1-0, p1-0/ 1-0-1-0-1-0, vp0-0-0-0-1-0-1, vr2-0/1-1-0-1-0-1, r1-1-1-1-1-1-0; metatarsus vp1-0-0-1-0-0-1, vr1-0-0-1-0-0-1, r0- 1-0-0-0-0-0; IV, femur d1-1-1-0/1-1-0/1-1-0, r0-0-0-0-0-0-1-0; tibia vp0-0-1/0-0-0-0-1, vr0-0-0-0-0-0-1, r0-0-0-0- 0-1/0-0; metatarsus p1-0-0-0-0-0-0, vp1-0-0-1-0-0-1, vr metatarsal comb with 4 macrosetae.

Female (
MHNS
836).

Coloration of carapace, chelicerae, endites, sternum and abdomen as in male (
Fig. 50F‒G
). Palps brownish orange, with tibia and tarsus reddish. Legs brownish orange, with pairs I‒II darker. Tibia, metatarsus e tarsus I‒II reddish orange (
Fig. 50H‒I
